description:
This is one of the targets I took during my 4-day camping at Lake San Antonio with my friends. I officially started to use my AP1100. I am really satisfied with this mount and will continue to optimize my setup and cable management. I also used some Ha data (Baader 7 nm filter) and O3 data I got last year. I like the combination of the bubble and its neighbor M52 cluster. 

Image details:
Mount: Astro-Physics 1100GTO
Telescope: Vixen ED103s+Astro Tech flattener
Camera: SBIG STF-8300 with OAG+FW8-8300 filter wheel
Guide camera: SBIG OAG-8300+Lodestar X2 with Kiss focuser
Filter: Astrodon LRGB Gen2 E-Series, Astrodon 3 nm Ha, Baader 7 nm Ha, Baader 8.5 nm O3
Exposure time:
L: 8*10 min,
R: 14*10 min,
G: 14*10 min,
B: 14*10 min,
Ha: 18*20 min
O3: 14*20 min
Post processing: Pixinsight 1.8.6+Photoshop
C&C are welcomes
title: Bubble nebula and his friend
